               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary>Although this manuscript bears a <locus facs="3">paper note</locus> stating that it is the dictionary of <term xml:lang="sa">Amarasiṃha</term>, it contains rather the text of the <title xml:lang="sa">Bhāgavatapurāṇa</title>, <term xml:lang="sa">skandha</term> 10, from the beginning of <term xml:lang="sa">adhyāya</term> 1 to the end of <term xml:lang="sa">adhyāya</term> 72. The first folio is unnumbered; folio numbering begins with the second folio, numbered 1 onwards. A number of folios are missing. A <locus facs="5">leaf</locus> from what seems to be a different manuscript, in Malayalam, has been inserted at the beginning.</summary>
                  
               <msItem defective="true"><title xml:lang="sa">Bhāgavatapurāṇa — skandha 10</title><textLang mainLang="san"/><rubric xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="0r" unit="folio" facs="9"/>
<lb n="1"/>hariḥ oṁ gaṇapataye namaḥ | avighnam astu | viṣṇurātaḥ |</rubric><incipit xml:lang="sa">kathito vaṃśavistaro bhavatā somasūryya<unclear>yoḥ</unclear> rājñāñ cobhayavaṃśyānāṃ caritaṃ paramātbhūtaṃ</incipit><explicit xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="107v" facs="186" unit="folio"/>
<lb n="9"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/>sadehadevan tattanayaṃ bhagavān_ bhūtabhāvanaḥ abhyaṣiñcad ameyātmā magadhānāṃ
<lb n="10"/><gap reason="lost"/></explicit></msItem></msContents>
